title="Alex Nelson">Alex Nelson</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> be a set of points on the plane containing the origin and two points <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[P]]></fr:tex>, <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[Q]]></fr:tex> such that their length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[|PQ|=1]]></fr:tex>. Let <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}]]></fr:tex> be the field generated over <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {Q}]]></fr:tex> by the coordinates of the points of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>. A length <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell ]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link
type="local"
href="nt-001F.xml"
addr="nt-001F"
title="Constructible length">constructible</fr:link> from <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex> if and only if there exists a finite sequence
<fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[\mathbb {F}=F_{0}\subset  F_{1}\subset …\subset  F_{n},]]></fr:tex>
where each <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{i}]]></fr:tex> is a quadratic extension of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F_{i-1}]]></fr:tex>, and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\ell \in  F_{n}]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
 
   
